 The bulk of African debt is owed to official lenders under various aid agreements.
 The debts represent loans with a substantial grant element.
 What I do know is that throughout Asia, Africa and Latin America the level of material achievement declines as we move away from the effect of western commerce.
 To harp on alleged external causes of Third World poverty diverts attention from the real factors behind this poverty which are domestic, and thereby from the possibilities of addressing these.
 It is pertinent also that the poorest are low among the priorities of the local rulers.
